# 3. 思わぬ奈落

Rui: We lift on three. One... Two... Three!
Tsukasa: Oof!
Nene: Oh...!
Emu: Whoa! Is that a trap door in the middle?!
Tsukasa: Hack! Cough! It's so dusty...! How did you know there was this space?
Rui: I found it by chance when tidying up.
Rui: It was probably used as storage for stage equipment.
Rui: A lucky find, wouldn't you say? We can use it as a trap room.
Emu: What's that?
Nene: A room beneath the stage that actors can use as an entrance or exit.
Rui: For example, I can hide one of my zombie robots here for when the play starts.
Rui: That can be where the story will reach its first climax as the zombie robot rise and make their appearance.
Rui: It'll be like they dug themselves out of the ground up, see?
Rui: The protagonist, Tsukasa, will fly into a panic and try to run away, but more zombie robots will appear from the seats to surround him...
Rui: There is no escape... And Tsukasa will be dragged into the trap room.
Rui: That's how I envision it. What do you think?
Emu: Ooh! That sounds awesome!!
Tsukasa: Hmm... Not bad. The more hair-raising the scene is, the more dramatic the plot twist will be!
Tsukasa: But you have to build the robots by yourself, Rui. Are you sure you can make them in time...?
Rui: Ah, but I already finished one.
Tsukasa: Already?!
Rui: I started building it as soon as I got this idea yesterday.
Nene: That explains the huge suitcase I saw you hauling around this morning.
Emu: So, we can start rehearsing right away?! Yay! Let's do it!
Rui: We can do a test run with my zombie robot while going over the main points of the play.
Tsukasa: Okay. For this one, your robot drags me away to the trap room, right?
Rui: Yes. I put a mat down there so you'll have a soft landing. The robot has built-in safety features, so there's no need to worry.
Emu: Good luck, Tsukasa!!
Zombie Robot: Augh... Augh...
Tsukasa: Yikes... I know it's just a robot but I'm still a bit creeped out...
Rui: Are you ready?
Tsukasa: Yeah! Here I go!
Tsukasa: Stop! I'm the director! You cannot treat me like this!
Zombie Robot: Augh... Augh...
Tsukasa: Stop... No... NOOO!
Nene: Hehe... Nice.
Rui: Yes. It went very smoothly.
Rui: Thanks, Tsukasa! That was perfect.
Tsukasa: You think so? A top performance from a top star!
Tsukasa: Okay, I'm going to climb back out. Heave-ho!
Zombie Robot: Augh... Augh...
Rui: Hm? Why is my robot still moving...?
Tsukasa: Argh! Let go of my clothes! No, I'm gonna...
Tsukasa: Aaargh!!
Emu: Tsukasa?! He fell back in!
Rui: ...!!
Nene: There's a mat on the floor, but... Are you okay?!
Emu: Tsukasaaa! He's not waking up! What do we do?
Rui: This is bad... Tsukasa!
Tsukasa: Gasp!
Nene: He's awake!
Emu: Thank goodness! Are you okay, Tsukasa?
Tsukasa: What... What happened?
Nene: The robot grabbed your clothes and you fell back into the trap room. Thankfully, you landed on the mat...
Rui: I'm sorry, Tsukasa. My robot seems to have malfunctioned...
Rui: I was convinced my safety features were foolproof but... It's all my fault.
Tsukasa: That could've ended really badly for me, you know!
Rui: ...
Tsukasa: But accidents happen...
Tsukasa: Next time, I'll make sure to be more careful too. I'd never forgive myself if an incident like this happened during a show and terrified our audience.
Tsukasa: To be clear, I think this dramatic scene is great! This is the kind of stuff I want to see more from you, Rui!
Rui: Yeah...
Tsukasa: You okay...?
